

Building the package
--------------------


in the main directory (../nandi)
run python setup.py install 

This will build the nandi package

You can locally install using 
"pip install ." from the package root.




# How to publish to pypi

Generate the files to upload to pypi with the followign cmd

"python setup.py sdist" in the directory where the setup resides

twine upload dist/nandi-0.2.tar.gz 


twine upload path-to-gzfile-generate-from python.setup install

twine upload dist/*

username for pypi 
snandi & TsainiK

